module: a1-08
level: A1
sequence: 8
slug: the-living-verb-ii
version: '2.0'
title: The Living Verb II
subtitle: Second Conjugation (-ити verbs)
content_outline:
- section: Warm-up
  points:
  - Second Conjugation — the -ити family (говорити, робити)
  - Still imperfective (ongoing/habitual actions)
  - Powers actions from speaking and seeing to loving
- section: Presentation
  points:
  - 'Pattern: -ити → -ю, -иш, -ить, -имо, -ите, -ять — Visual Paradigms: Compare 1st
    (читати) vs 2nd (говорити) side-by-side to highlight vowel difference (е/є vs
    и/і)'
  - 'Example paradigm: говорити → говорю, говориш, говорить...'
  - 'Consonant mutations in some verbs (д→дж, т→ч) — State Standard: сидіти (сиджу...);
    frame ''labial L'' (роблю, люблю) as a helpful sound for easier pronunciation,
    not just an exception'
  - 'Common verbs (робити, бачити, любити, ходити) — include їсти and пити as ''Bonus
    Verbs''; learner error: Conjugation Mix-up (using 1st conjugation endings like
    роб-еш)'
- section: Practice
  points:
  - Conjugation drills with -ити verbs
  - Sorting verbs by conjugation (1st vs 2nd)
- section: Production
  points:
  - 'Describing what people do (Вона бачить, Вони люблять) — use collocations: робити
    помилки, любити читати, бачити світ'
- section: Cultural Insight
  points:
  - 'The -ити ending is over 1000 years old (Proto-Slavic) — Proto-Slavic Roots: Direct
    descendant of *-iti class, structurally recognizable for 1000+ years'
  - 'Shared with Polish, Czech, and other Slavic languages — The Etymology of ''Любити'':
    Shares roots with ''люди'' (people), implying to love is to be part of the community'
vocabulary_hints:
  required:
  - говорити (to speak) — говорити українською, говорити повільно
  - робити (to do) — робити помилки, робити вибір
  - любити (to love) — любити читати, любити музику
  - бачити (to see) — бачити світ, бачити сон
  - 'їсти (to eat) — хочу їсти, готувати їсти; learner error: attempting regular conjugation
    (я їджу)'
  - пити (to drink) — пити каву, пити воду
  - ходити (to walk) — ходити в парк, ходити до школи
  - просити (to ask)
  recommended:
  - сидіти (to sit) — State Standard example for consonant mutation (сиджу)
  - стояти (to stand)
  - платити (to pay)
  - вчити (to teach/learn)
activity_hints:
- type: fill-in
  focus: Conjugate Second Conjugation verbs
  items: 30
- type: match-up
  focus: Sort verbs by conjugation type
  items: 20
- type: fill-in
  focus: Complete with mutated forms
  items: 15
focus: grammar
pedagogy: PPP
prerequisites:
- a1-06 (The Living Verb I)
- a1-07 (Questions and Negation)
connects_to:
- a1-09 (Reflexive Verbs)
- a1-21 (Past Tense)
objectives:
- Learner can conjugate Second Conjugation verbs (-ити) in present tense
- Learner can distinguish between First and Second Conjugation
- Learner can use common irregular verbs (їсти, пити)
- Learner can form basic sentences with action verbs
grammar:
- Second Conjugation pattern (-ити → -у, -иш...)
- Consonant mutation patterns
- Irregular verbs
register: розмовний
phase: A1.1 [First Contact]
persona:
  voice: Patient Supportive Tutor
  role: Choreographer
word_target: 2000
